#. <section class="sutta" id="an7.16"><article><div class="hgroup"><p class="division">
msgctxt "an7.16:0.1"
msgid "Aṅguttara Nikāya 7"
msgstr "Numbered Discourses 7"

#. </p><p>
msgctxt "an7.16:0.2"
msgid "2. Anusayavagga"
msgstr "2. Tendencies"

#. </p><h1>
msgctxt "an7.16:0.3"
msgid "16. Aniccānupassīsutta"
msgstr "16. Observing Impermanence"

#. </h1></div><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc1"></a>
msgctxt "an7.16:1.1"
msgid ""
"“Sattime, bhikkhave, puggalā āhuneyyā pāhuneyyā dakkhiṇeyyā añjalikaraṇīyā "
"anuttaraṃ puññakkhettaṃ lokassa."
msgstr ""
"“Mendicants, these seven people are worthy of offerings dedicated to the "
"gods, worthy of hospitality, worthy of a teacher’s offering, worthy of "
"greeting with joined palms, and are the supreme field of merit for the world."

msgctxt "an7.16:1.2"
msgid "Katame satta?"
msgstr "What seven?"

msgctxt "an7.16:1.3"
msgid ""
"Idha, bhikkhave, ekacco puggalo sabbasaṅkhāresu aniccānupassī viharati, "
"aniccasaññī, aniccapaṭisaṃvedī satataṃ samitaṃ abbokiṇṇaṃ cetasā "
"adhimuccamāno paññāya pariyogāhamāno."
msgstr ""
"First, take a person who meditates observing impermanence in all conditions. "
"They perceive impermanence and experience impermanence. Constantly, "
"continually, and without stopping, they apply the mind and fathom with "
"wisdom."

msgctxt "an7.16:1.4"
msgid "So āsavānaṃ khayā … pe … sacchikatvā upasampajja viharati."
msgstr ""
"They’ve realized the undefiled freedom of heart and freedom by wisdom in "
"this very life, and live having realized it with their own insight due to "
"the ending of defilements."

msgctxt "an7.16:1.5"
msgid ""
"Ayaṃ, bhikkhave, paṭhamo puggalo āhuneyyo pāhuneyyo dakkhiṇeyyo "
"añjalikaraṇīyo anuttaraṃ puññakkhettaṃ lokassa."
msgstr "This is the first person."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc2"></a>
msgctxt "an7.16:2.1"
msgid ""
"Puna caparaṃ, bhikkhave, idhekacco puggalo sabbasaṅkhāresu aniccānupassī "
"viharati, aniccasaññī, aniccapaṭisaṃvedī satataṃ samitaṃ abbokiṇṇaṃ cetasā "
"adhimuccamāno paññāya pariyogāhamāno."
msgstr ""
"Next, take a person who meditates observing impermanence in all conditions."

msgctxt "an7.16:2.2"
msgid "Tassa apubbaṃ acarimaṃ āsavapariyādānañca hoti jīvitapariyādānañca."
msgstr ""
"Their defilements and their life come to an end at exactly the same time."

msgctxt "an7.16:2.3"
msgid ""
"Ayaṃ, bhikkhave, dutiyo puggalo āhuneyyo … pe … anuttaraṃ puññakkhettaṃ "
"lokassa."
msgstr "This is the second person."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="pts-vp-pli" id="pts-vp-pli4.14"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc3"></a>
msgctxt "an7.16:3.1"
msgid ""
"Puna caparaṃ, bhikkhave, idhekacco puggalo sabbasaṅkhāresu aniccānupassī "
"viharati, aniccasaññī, aniccapaṭisaṃvedī satataṃ samitaṃ abbokiṇṇaṃ cetasā "
"adhimuccamāno paññāya pariyogāhamāno."
msgstr ""
"Next, take a person who meditates observing impermanence in all conditions."

msgctxt "an7.16:3.2"
msgid ""
"So pañcannaṃ orambhāgiyānaṃ saṃyojanānaṃ parikkhayā antarāparinibbāyī hoti … "
"pe …"
msgstr ""
"With the ending of the five lower fetters they’re extinguished in-between "
"one life and the next. …"

msgctxt "an7.16:3.3"
msgid "upahaccaparinibbāyī hoti … pe …"
msgstr ""
"With the ending of the five lower fetters they’re extinguished upon landing. "
"…"

msgctxt "an7.16:3.4"
msgid "asaṅkhāraparinibbāyī hoti … pe …"
msgstr ""
"With the ending of the five lower fetters they’re extinguished without extra "
"effort. …"

msgctxt "an7.16:3.5"
msgid "sasaṅkhāraparinibbāyī hoti … pe …"
msgstr ""
"With the ending of the five lower fetters they’re extinguished with extra "
"effort. …"

msgctxt "an7.16:3.6"
msgid "uddhaṃsoto hoti akaniṭṭhagāmī."
msgstr ""
"With the ending of the five lower fetters they head upstream, going to the "
"Akaniṭṭha realm."

msgctxt "an7.16:3.7"
msgid ""
"Ayaṃ, bhikkhave, sattamo puggalo āhuneyyo pāhuneyyo dakkhiṇeyyo "
"añjalikaraṇīyo anuttaraṃ puññakkhettaṃ lokassa."
msgstr "This is the seventh person"

msgctxt "an7.16:3.8"
msgid ""
"Ime kho, bhikkhave, satta puggalā āhuneyyā pāhuneyyā dakkhiṇeyyā "
"añjalikaraṇīyā anuttaraṃ puññakkhettaṃ lokassā”ti."
msgstr ""
"These are the seven people who are worthy of offerings dedicated to the "
"gods, worthy of hospitality, worthy of a teacher’s offering, worthy of "
"greeting with joined palms, and are the supreme field of merit for the "
"world.”"

#. </p><p class="endsection">
msgctxt "an7.16:3.9"
msgid "Chaṭṭhaṃ."
msgstr ""
